channel.title: JBoss Issue Tracker
channel.description: This file is an XML representation of an issue

item.title: [WFLY-5140] NoClassDefFoundError in ha configuration
item.description:
When testing our app with JMeter (5 concurrent users) plenty (hundreds in single request, no kidding) NoClassDefFoundErrors occur. From the client side they are visible as 500 - internal server errors. Unfortunately those errors are not easily reproducible. Not every test run is affected. Actually, I was not able to reproduce them in manual tests, just in JMeter.

The cluster consists of three servers in HA profile.

Stacktrace example:

                </cache-container>
 
            </subsystem>

The only thing that would cause such a NoClassDefFoundError is if org.infinispan.commands.remote.recovery.TxCompletionNotificationCommand imported some class that wasn't available from the owning module (i.e. org.infinispan). The obvious culprit should be javax.transaction.api, but this is clearly not the case.
https://github.com/wildfly/wildfly/blob/9.0.1.Final/feature-pack/src/main/resources/modules/system/layers/base/org/infinispan/main/module.xml
We would also have immediately noticed such a failure in our integration testsuite - which is also not the case.

This leads me to believe that the real culprit is JMeter itself. I'm not sure how well JMeter behaves in WildFly's modular class loading environment.

I didn't mention it earlier, but on older jdk (1.8u51) there was another error: StackOverflowError. It appeared only once per server run and was the very first error in the log file.
